Joseph Olaoluwa Executive Director, Shared Services and Products of Fidelity Bank Plc, Chijioke Ugochukwu, is set to quit her position as director after 30 years. Ugochukwu is stepping down from the position because her contract tenure as director of the bank would expire on March 31, 2020. In a statement filed by the bank to the Nigerian Stock Exchange, the lender expressed appreciation to her for the contributions she made for the bankâ€™s growth. The bank noted that Ugochukwu joined the bank as a member of the National Youth Service Corps in 1989, employed as an executive trainee in 1990 and culminated in her appointment to the Board on April 1, 2012. It added that the Central Bank of Nigeria and the Securities and Exchange Commission were privy to the development. Copyright PUNCH.
